#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.185"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.185:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.185:0.2"
msgid "19. Brāhmaṇavagga "
msgstr "19. Brahmins "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: catukoṭikasuññatāsuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.185:0.3"
msgid "185. Brāhmaṇasaccasutta "
msgstr "185. Truths of the Brahmins "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.185:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate. "
msgstr "Once the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.185:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā paribbājakā sippinikātīre paribbājakārāme paṭivasanti, seyyathidaṃ annabhāro varadharo sakuludāyī ca paribbājako aññe ca abhiññātā abhiññātā paribbājakā. "
msgstr "Now at that time several very well-known wanderers were residing in the monastery of the wanderers on the bank of the Sappinī river. They included Annabhāra, Varadhara, Sakuludāyī, and other very well-known wanderers. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.185:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena sippinikātīre paribbājakārāmo tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the wanderer’s monastery on the bank of the Sappinī river. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.185:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarā kathā udapādi: "
msgstr "Now at that time this discussion came up while those wanderers who follow other paths were sitting together, "

msgctxt "an4.185:2.2"
msgid "“itipi brāhmaṇasaccāni, itipi brāhmaṇasaccānī”ti. "
msgstr "“The truths of the brahmins are like this; the truths of the brahmins are like that.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.185:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā yena te paribbājakā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja kho bhagavā te paribbājake etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha went up to those wanderers, sat down on the seat spread out, and said to them, "

#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.185:3.1"
msgid "“Kāya nuttha, paribbājakā, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā, kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti? "
msgstr "“Wanderers, what were you sitting talking about just now? What conversation was unfinished?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.185:3.2"
msgid "“Idha, bho gotama, amhākaṃ sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi: "
msgstr "“Well, Master Gotama, this discussion came up among us while we were sitting together: "

msgctxt "an4.185:3.3"
msgid "‘itipi brāhmaṇasaccāni, itipi brāhmaṇasaccānī’”ti. "
msgstr "‘The truths of the brahmins are like this; the truths of the brahmins are like that.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.185:4.1"
msgid "“Cattārimāni, paribbājakā, brāhmaṇasaccāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni. "
msgstr "“Wanderers, I declare these four truths of the brahmins, having realized them with my own insight. "

msgctxt "an4.185:4.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.185:4.3"
msgid "Idha, paribbājakā, brāhmaṇo evamāha: "
msgstr "Take a brahmin who says: "

msgctxt "an4.185:4.4"
msgid "‘sabbe pāṇā avajjhā’ti. "
msgstr "‘No sentient beings should be killed.’ "

msgctxt "an4.185:4.5"
msgid "Iti vadaṃ brāhmaṇo saccaṃ āha, no musā. "
msgstr "Saying this, a brahmin speaks the truth, not lies. "

msgctxt "an4.185:4.6"
msgid "So tena na samaṇoti maññati, na brāhmaṇoti maññati, na seyyohamasmīti maññati, na sadisohamasmīti maññati, na hīnohamasmīti maññati. "
msgstr "But they don’t think of themselves as an ‘ascetic’ or ‘brahmin’ because of that. Nor do they think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’. "

#. VAR: pāṇānaṃyeva anuddayāya → pāṇānaṃyeva anudayāya (s1-3) | tadabhiññāya anudayāya (mr)
msgctxt "an4.185:4.7"
msgid "Api ca yadeva tattha saccaṃ tadabhiññāya pāṇānaṃyeva anuddayāya anukampāya paṭipanno hoti. "
msgstr "Rather, they simply practice out of kindness and compassion for living creatures, having had insight into the truth of that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.177, sc5
msgctxt "an4.185:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, paribbājakā, brāhmaṇo evamāha: "
msgstr "Take another brahmin who says: "

msgctxt "an4.185:5.2"
msgid "‘sabbe kāmā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā’ti. "
msgstr "‘All sensual pleasures are impermanent, suffering, and perishable.’ "

msgctxt "an4.185:5.3"
msgid "Iti vadaṃ brāhmaṇo saccamāha, no musā. "
msgstr "Saying this, a brahmin speaks the truth, not lies. "

msgctxt "an4.185:5.4"
msgid "So tena na samaṇoti maññati, na brāhmaṇoti maññati, na seyyohamasmīti maññati, na sadisohamasmīti maññati, na hīnohamasmīti maññati. "
msgstr "But they don’t think of themselves as an ‘ascetic’ or ‘brahmin’ because of that. Nor do they think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’. "

msgctxt "an4.185:5.5"
msgid "Api ca yadeva tattha saccaṃ tadabhiññāya kāmānaṃyeva nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti. "
msgstr "Rather, they simply practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding sensual pleasures, having had insight into the truth of that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an4.185:6.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, paribbājakā, brāhmaṇo evamāha: "
msgstr "Take another brahmin who says: "

msgctxt "an4.185:6.2"
msgid "‘sabbe bhavā aniccā … pe … tadabhiññāya bhavānaṃyeva nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti. "
msgstr "‘All states of existence are impermanent, suffering, and perishable.’ … They simply practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding future lives, having had insight into the truth of that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an4.185:7.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, paribbājakā, brāhmaṇo evamāha: "
msgstr "Take another brahmin who says: "

#. VAR: kvacani → kvacana (bj) | kvacini (s1-3) | kvaci (pts1)
msgctxt "an4.185:7.2"
msgid "‘nāhaṃ kvacani kassaci kiñcanatasmiṃ na ca mama kvacani katthaci kiñcanatatthī’ti. "
msgstr "‘I don’t belong to anyone anywhere. And nothing belongs to me anywhere.’ "

msgctxt "an4.185:7.3"
msgid "Iti vadaṃ brāhmaṇo saccaṃ āha, no musā. "
msgstr "Saying this, a brahmin speaks the truth, not lies. "

msgctxt "an4.185:7.4"
msgid "So tena na samaṇoti maññati, na brāhmaṇoti maññati, na seyyohamasmīti maññati, na sadisohamasmīti maññati, na hīnohamasmīti maññati. "
msgstr "But they don’t think of themselves as an ‘ascetic’ or ‘brahmin’ because of that. Nor do they think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’. "

msgctxt "an4.185:7.5"
msgid "Api ca yadeva tattha saccaṃ tadabhiññāya ākiñcaññaṃyeva paṭipadaṃ paṭipanno hoti. "
msgstr "Rather, they simply practice the path of nothingness, having had insight into the truth of that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.185:7.6"
msgid "Imāni kho, paribbājakā, cattāri brāhmaṇasaccāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditānī”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four truths of the brahmins that I declare, having realized them with my own insight.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.185:7.7"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
